Commonwealth Chesapeake Company, LLC FERC Electric Tariff, Volume No. 1
1. Availability: Commonwealth Chesapeake Company, LLC makes available at wholesale under this Tariff:
a. Electric energy and capacity; and
b. Ancillary services as specified below:
(1) PJM: Commonwealth Chesapeake Company, LLC offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection; and
(2) Third-party ancillary services include Regulation and Frequency Response Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, and Operating Reserve-Supplemental. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation and Frequency Response Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider's OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization.
2. Applicability: This Tariff applies to all wholesale sales of electric energy, capacity and ancillary services by Commonwealth Chesapeake Company, LLC not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule or contract of Commonwealth Chesapeake Company, LLC.
3. Rate: Sales made under this Tariff shall be at rates established by agreement between Commonwealth Chesapeake Company, LLC and the purchaser.
4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions of the sale shall be established by agreement between Commonwealth Chesapeake Company, LLC and the purchaser.
5. Effective Date: Unless the appropriate regulatory body orders otherwise, this FERC Electric Tariff, Volume No. 1 is effective as of this in-service date of the generating facility owned by Commonwealth Chesapeake Company, LLC.
6. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes seller to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
7. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: Seller has received waiver of: Subparts Band C of Part 35, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; Part 41, Part 101, and Part 141, except sections 141.14 and 141.15; and received blanket approval under Part 34. See Commonwealth Chesapeake Company, LLC, 85 FERC 61,404, at 62,545 (1998).
8. Seller Category: Commonwealth Chesapeake Company, LLC is a Category 2 Seller in the Northeast region and a Category 1 Seller in all other regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a).
